data.description: Welcome home to 3546 Briarwood Drive, a stylish and well-maintained Picasso model townhome style condo, just a stone's throw away from Quantico and 30 Minutes from the Pentagon!  With a 1-car garage and additional parking space, you can easily commute into DC by hopping on I-95, taking the VRE or using the convenient 234 commuter lot adjacent to the neighborhood.  This home is a perfect blend of modern luxury and practical functionality.  The main level features gorgeous recently upgraded porcelain tile flooring (2022) and includes an open kitchen concept with dining area and family room seamlessly connected.  The kitchen is a culinary delight, with its sleek and spacious generous center island offering an overhang for bar stool seating, granite countertops, newly added glass-tile backsplash, and modern 42-inch cabinetry in a chic black finish.  A built-in desk area with organizational shelving adds convenience, and stainless steel appliances, including a double wall oven, make cooking a breeze.  Plus, there's a stylish range hood!  Step outside onto the balcony off the kitchen, perfect for enjoying early morning coffee or evening relaxation as the weather gets warmer.  Ascending the hardwood stairs to the upper level, three bedrooms offer comfort and style, with new (2022) carpet on the entire level.  French doors lead you into the airy owner’s suite where you’ll find ample closet space with its TWO walk-in closets, a tray ceiling and en-suite bath with a Kohler deep soaking tub, dual granite vanities and separate shower - providing the relaxing atmosphere you need at the end of a long day.  The other two bedrooms on this level share an updated hall bath with a double-sink granite vanity, new white subway tile in the shower/tub, and porcelain floors.  The second bedroom features a sizable walk-in closet, and the cute laundry room is located on the bedroom level for easy convenience.  It includes a counter for folding and custom built-in cabinetry to neatly stow your belongings.  The HVAC closet also resides on this level - Just serviced in Jan. 2024.  Conveniently located near Stonebridge at Potomac Town Center with all its shopping and restaurants.  For the nature enthusiasts it’s close to the Neabsco Regional Trail and boardwalk over Neabsco Creek, close to Potomac River, Leesylvania Park, and Prince William Forest.  This townhouse is not just a home; it's a lifestyle.  This home was just built in 2018 and has barely been lived in!  With its thoughtful design and proximity to Quantico, it's an opportunity not to be missed.  Schedule your showing today and envision yourself living in this perfect blend of comfort and sophistication.
